This class represents a PlayableCard which can be one of the resource, gold or base ones

    • PlayableCard

      public PlayableCard(int id, int points, AngleType front_up_right, AngleType front_up_left, AngleType front_down_right, AngleType front_down_left, AngleType back_up_right, AngleType back_up_left, AngleType back_down_right, AngleType back_down_left, List<AngleType> centralResources, boolean coverAngleToReceivePoints, boolean haveFeatherToReceivePoints, boolean haveScrollToReceivePoints, boolean haveJarToReceivePoints, Map<AngleType,Integer> neededResources)
      Class constructor This method creates an instance of different types of playableCards
      Parameters:
      id - cardID
      points - card's points
      front_up_right - is the resource in the specified corner
      front_up_left - is the resource in the specified corner
      front_down_right - is the resource in the specified corner
      front_down_left - is the resource in the specified corner
      back_up_right - is the resource in the specified corner
      back_up_left - is the resource in the specified corner
      back_down_right - is the resource in the specified corner
      back_down_left - is the resource in the specified corner
      centralResources - are the resources in the center of the card
      coverAngleToReceivePoints - if it gives points related to the angles covered when placed
      haveFeatherToReceivePoints - if it gives points related to Feather count when placed
      haveScrollToReceivePoints - if it gives points related to Scroll count when placed
      haveJarToReceivePoints - if it gives points related to Jar count when placed
      neededResources - are the resources needed to place the card
